==English==

===Etymology===
From {{inh|en|enm|schal}} (infinitive {{m|enm|schulen}}), from {{inh|en|ang|sċeal}} (infinitive {{m|ang|sċulan||to be obligated or obliged to, shall, must, owe, ought to}}), from {{inh|en|gem-pro|*skal}} (infinitive {{m|gem-pro|*skulaną}}), from {{der|en|ine-pro|*skel-||to owe, be under obligation}}. Cognate with {{cog|sco|sall}}, {{m|sco|sal||shall}}, {{cog|fy|sil}} (infinitive {{m|fy|sille||shall}}), {{cog|nl|zal}} (infinitive {{m|nl|zullen||shall}}), {{cog|nds|schall}} (infinitive {{m|nds-de|schölen||shall}}), {{cog|de|soll}} (infinitive {{m|de|sollen||ought to}}), {{cog|da|skal}} (infinitive {{m|da|skulle||shall}}), {{cog|is|skal}} (infinitive {{m|is|skulu|t=shall}}). Related to {{l|en|shild}}.

